The World Gold Council (WGC) has started 2023 with the addition of two new members – Pan American Silver and Osisko Gold Royalties. WGC chairperson Randy Smallwood comments that the companies’ experience and expertise across the Americas will bring a wealth of knowledge and insight to the board of members. Pan American owns and operates silver and gold mines located in Mexico, Peru, Canada, Argentina and Bolivia. Osisko is a precious metals royalty company that holds a North America-focused portfolio of more than 180 royalties, streams and precious metals offtakes.